t, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Somerton, Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Stansfield, West Suffolk district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Stansfield, Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Saint Margaret's Church, Somerton, Babergh district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"St Margaret's Church, Somerton, Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Stamfield Suffolk England":"Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1415–1494":"1415–1494","1420–1497":"1420–1497","1432–Male":"1432–Deceased","1436–1494":"1436–1494","1440–1442":"1440–1442","1445–Male":"1445–Deceased","1765–Female":"1765–Deceased","1415":"1415","1436":"1436","1447":"1447","1765":"1765","1445":"1445","1432":"1432","1442":"1442","1497":"1497","1420":"1420","1440":"1440","1494":"1494","Somerton, Babergh district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Somerton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Stansfield, West Suffolk district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Stansfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Saint Margaret's Church, Somerton, Babergh district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"St Margaret's Church, Somerton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Stamfield Suffolk England":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Roslin","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (southern Wales): from a double diminutive of <i>Rob</i> or <i>Rab</i>, both pet forms of the Middle English personal name   Robert  , the latter with dialect unrounding of /-o-/.","French: from a shortened form of <i>Robelin</i>, a diminutive of the personal name   Robert  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Robert","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Marcel, Gilles, Normand, Armand, Lucien, Pierre, Emile, Michel, Edouard, Gaston, Yves.","French, Walloon, English, German, Dutch, Flemish, and Breton (of French origin); Hungarian (<b>Róbert</b>): from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Ro(d)bert</i> (Middle English <i>Robert</i>, Old French <i>Ro(d)bert</i>), composed of the elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame, renown’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This is found occasionally in Anglo-Saxon England before the Conquest, but in the main it was introduced into England by the Normans and quickly became popular among all classes of society. Pet forms and diminutives are found from an early date,   Robin   being particularly common. Compare   Robair  ,   Robar  ,   Robare  , and   Rober  .","In some cases also an Americanized form of one or more similar (like-sounding) Jewish surnames."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Roslin was born in 1415, in Stansfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She married John Griggs Jr. in 1447, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons. She died in 1494, in Somerton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 79, and was buried in St Margaret's Church, Somerton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1415–1494":"1415–1494","1420–1497":"1420–1497","1432–Male":"1432–Surnud","1436–1494":"1436–1494","1440–1442":"1440–1442","1445–Male":"1445–Surnud","1765–Female":"1765–Surnud","1415":"1415","1436":"1436","1447":"1447","1765":"1765","1445":"1445","1432":"1432","1442":"1442","1497":"1497","1420":"1420","1440":"1440","1494":"1494","Somerton, Babergh district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Somerton, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stansfield, West Suffolk district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Stansfield, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Saint Margaret's Church, Somerton, Babergh district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"St Margaret's Church, Somerton, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stamfield Suffolk England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1415–1494":"1415–1494","1420–1497":"1420–1497","1432–Male":"1432–Kuollut","1436–1494":"1436–1494","1440–1442":"1440–1442","1445–Male":"1445–Kuollut","1765–Female":"1765–Kuollut","1415":"1415","1436":"1436","1447":"1447","1765":"1765","1445":"1445","1432":"1432","1442":"1442","1497":"1497","1420":"1420","1440":"1440","1494":"1494","Somerton, Babergh district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Somerton, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stansfield, West Suffolk district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Stansfield, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuning